-- Gold Fields, Harmony, Mondi, Sasol May Move: South African Equity Preview
-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 2010-11-01T05:35:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-01/gold-fields-harmony-mondi-sasol-may-move-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose for a second day,
adding 244.32, or 0.8 percent, to 30,430.90 in Johannesburg.  FirstRand Ltd.  (FSR SJ): South Africa’s second-biggest
financial-services company said the deadline for meeting
conditions for the merger of Metropolitan Holdings Ltd. and
Momentum Group Ltd. has been extended to Nov. 30. Shares rose 19
cents, or 0.9 percent, to 20.61 rand.  Gold Fields Ltd.  (GFI SJ): Gold may decline on concern that
prices rose too high amid speculation about Federal Reserve
asset purchases, a Bloomberg survey of 26 traders found. Gold
Fields, Africa’s second-largest producer of the metal, gained
2.63 rand, or 2.5 percent, to 109.62 rand.  AngloGold Ashanti
Ltd. , Africa’s biggest gold producer, climbed 4.24 rand, or 1.3
percent, to 32,649 rand.  Harmony Gold Mining Ltd.  (HAR SJ): The third-largest
producer of the metal in Africa releases first-quarter earnings.
The stock rose 2.01 rand, or 2.6 percent, to 80.20 rand.  Mondi Ltd.  (MND SJ): Europe’s largest maker of office paper
publishes its interim management statement. Mondi gained 20
cents, or 0.3 percent, to 58.20 rand.  Sasol Ltd.  (SOL SJ): Crude oil fell as the dollar rose
against the euro, reducing the appeal of raw materials as an
alternative investment. Shares in Sasol, the world’s biggest
maker of motor fuel from coal, dropped 2.28 rand, or 0.7
percent, to 315.41 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of South African
companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) added 1.1 percent to $23.25.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) rose 1.4 percent to $47.11. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) dropped 0.4 percent to $70.80. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) gained 0.2 percent to $4.92. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) climbed 2.2 percent to $15.77. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) jumped 2.2 percent to $11.5275. Impala Platinum
Holdings (IMPUY US) added 3 percent to $28.40. Sappi Ltd. (SPP
US) declined 0.2 percent to $4.97. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) fell 0.3
percent to $45.25.  The following share begins trading without the right to its
latest dividend:  PSG Group Ltd. (PSG SJ).  To contact the reporter on this story:
